:::summary
The Dead Sea Scrolls are a collection of approximately 981 ancient Jewish manuscripts discovered between 1947 and 1956 in caves near Qumran on the northwest shore of the Dead Sea. Dating from the third century BC to the first century AD, they are the oldest known manuscripts of the Hebrew Bible and contain writings from a Jewish sectarian community. Their discovery is considered the greatest archaeological find of the twentieth century.
:::

